It is not clear what capacity Renamo has, but it has already carried out destructive and rapid attacks on police stations and vehicles on a key motorway from north to south.
Most of the clashes took place in Sofala Province, which is several hundred kilometres north of Maputo, but includes Beira, a port that mining companies, including Rio Tinto and Vale, use to export coal.
