Further parties describe in different ways.
Roskomnadzor, based on the videos found, accused Rosbalt of a gross and systematic violation of the media law and requested the court to withdraw the licence from the agency.
In Rosbalt, it was argued that the agency's claims were unlawful: first, the rollers were not editorial materials, secondly, the words were disguised and, thirdly, immediately after warning, they were removed from the site.
The agency appealed Roskomnadzor ' s claims to the Magistrate ' s Court, and when Mosgorsud accepted Roskomnadzor ' s claim on 22 October 2013, these complaints were still pending.
